-ranging, critical work distinguishes between myths that sustain neocolonial orders and fictions that generate new forms of political and ethical life.  aDescription based on information from publisher. 0aSociological jurisprudence. 0aSovereigntyxSocial aspects. 0aBritish Indian Ocean TerritoryxInternational statusxSocial aspects. 0aChagossiansxLegal status, laws, etc.xSocial aspects. 0aRefugeesxLegal status, laws, etc.xSocial aspectszAustralia. 0aAboriginal AustraliansxLegal status, laws, etc.xSocial aspects. 0aTransitional justicexSocial aspectszSouth Africa. 0aPost-apartheid erazSouth Africa. 4aElectronic books.22aMichigan Publishing (University of Michigan)eissuing body,epublisher. 0aLaw, meaning, and violence.40zAccess to the Michigan Publishing online version:uhttps://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.7218743